{
  "stem": "20021.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 344.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And strangely, when I was in Hungary years later and I tried to tell people, look, this is what happened in Poland, again they would rather fall for false hopes then face the consequences, which meant, for instance, in this specific case running to Romania with me, the way I did.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But that meant abandoning home, everything, and going and suddenly be-- be a, you know--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the face of that terrible reality, they prefer to fool themselves.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's maybe human nature.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And Hitler took great advantage of that throughout.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And starting from those days that you just asked me in Poland, this was prevalent.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nobody faced up to that reality.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nobody wanted to, really, because if they had faced up, maybe they didn't have much option, but they probably would have had some options, or at least some people would have had some options and could have saved themselves.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What-- how early was life affected in Tarnow for the Jews by the rise to power of Hitler?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Directly, was not affected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But anti-Semitism grew stronger and stronger.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In other words, Hitler served sort of like an example for those who call themselves Nationalists.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, Hitler's movement was a nationalistic movement.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He called himself National Socialist.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was the official name of the Nazi Party.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had a lot of followers in Poland who were building organizations on the same theme that he was building, you know, nationalism being a strong force all together, even all the way 'til today.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So in that sense, he had an impact on all of Europe, France and Poland, Czechoslovakia, and so forth, that nationalistic parties were springing up all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
